    "objectives": "The aim of this IDM is to define the minimum information that must be exchanged between design authoring tools (e.g., architectural BIM software) and cost estimation tools when performing window cost estimation. The scope covers all window types in building envelopes including fixed, casement, sliding, tilt-and-turn, and curtain wall windows. It addresses supply costs, installation costs, and cost classification references. Sub-structure works such as wall openings, reveals, and lintels are out of scope.",
    "aimAndScope": "The aim of this IDM is to define the minimum information that must be exchanged between design authoring tools (e.g., architectural BIM software) and cost estimation tools when performing window cost estimation. The scope covers all window types in building envelopes including fixed, casement, sliding, tilt-and-turn, and curtain wall windows. It addresses supply costs, installation costs, and cost classification references. Sub-structure works such as wall openings, reveals, and lintels are out of scope.",
    "benefits": "Enables automated extraction of window quantities and properties from BIM models, reducing manual take-off effort and improving cost estimation accuracy. Supports early cost feedback during the design phase and provides a structured basis for procurement planning and tender documentation.",
    "limitations": "This IDM does not cover specialist glazing systems requiring bespoke structural engineering (e.g., structural glass fins, electrochromic glass). Costs for ancillary works such as reveals, sub-sills, and lintels are outside the scope. Regional price variations must be accounted for separately by the cost estimator.",
